  "texts": [
    "A more detailed overview with the proportion of each response option by group is depicted in Figure 8.",
    "Respondents in the PwD group gave either high or low scores to the items \"Ease of use\", \"Voice control\", \"Empathy\", and \"Human in the loop\", whereas supporters overwhelmingly gave high scores to these items.",
    "Overall mean score across all features and priorities was significantly correlated with age for PwD (r = -0.54, p = 0.04) but not supporters (p = 0.5).",
    "For PwD, when performing the same analyses on the score for each feature and priority separately, we found no significant relationships (all p > 0.05).",
    "There was no significant correlation with sex (PwD: p = 0.22, supporters: p = 0.17) and for PwD there was no correlation with the number of years since diagnosis (p = 0.33)."
  ],
